Violin plot of Features:
Violin plots of nine genes selected from the top principal component drivers revealed distinct expression patterns across the five timepoints. Neuronal marker S100a5 and fibroblast marker Col1a2 showed the highest absolute expression levels consistent with their abundance in the dataset. Myeloid markers Tyrobp and Cst3 showed subtle elevation at early infection timepoints D02 and D05, consistent with the immediate innate immune activation documented in the source paper. Endothelial marker Flt1 and macrophage marker C1qc maintained low but consistent expression across all timepoints reflecting their roles as stable structural and tissue-resident populations respectively. Epithelial markers Krt18 and Prdx6 remained broadly consistent throughout infection, suggesting maintained epithelial integrity across timepoints.

Feature Plot 
Feature plots of nine genes selected from the top loading genes of principal components 1-5 revealed spatially distinct expression patterns consistent with the major cell lineages of the nasal mucosa. The myeloid marker Tyrobp, dendritic cell marker Cst3, and macrophage marker C1qc co-localised in lower right UMAP clusters confirming the myeloid identity of these populations. The neuronal marker S100a5 showed strong concentrated expression in the large left UMAP region consistent with the abundant olfactory sensory neuron population. Fibroblast markers Col1a2 and Sparc were restricted to a distinct upper left cluster spatially separated from immune populations. The endothelial marker Flt1 showed highly specific expression in a single isolated cluster confirming endothelial cell identity. Epithelial markers Krt18 and Prdx6 showed broader expression across multiple clusters reflecting the transcriptional diversity of nasal epithelial cell subtypes described in the source paper.
